ll,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe common carotid artery bifurcates into the internal and external carotid arteries at the level of the \u003Cstrong\u003EC4\u003C/strong\u003E vertebra. This anatomical landmark is important for clinicians, especially during procedures involving the neck.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC2\u003C/strong\u003E - This level is higher in the neck and does not correspond to the bifurcation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC3\u003C/strong\u003E - This level is slightly higher than the typical bifurcation point\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC5\u003C/strong\u003E - This level is lower in the neck and below the bifurcation point\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC6\u003C/strong\u003E - This level is even lower and does not correspond to the bifurcation\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The common carotid artery bifurcates into the internal and external carotid arteries at the level of the C4 vertebra.","The bifurcation of the common carotid artery is an important anatomical landmark in the neck."],"references":["Fehrenbach, M. J., \u0026 Herring, S. W. (2015). Illustrated Anatomy of the Head and Neck-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534836/","Cramer, G. D., \u0026 Darby, S. A. (2013). Clinical anatomy of the spine, spinal cord, and ANS","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58793"}},"que